            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "The quality of study material and teaching methodology is not up to the expected standard. There are frequent holidays, which affects the continuity of learning. There is no proper ERP system for assigning or tracking homework—only in name, not in practice.\nThe school is named St. Stephen’s, but it does not reflect the standards or quality associated with the original St. Stephen’s College.\nThe facilities provided are not justified by the high fees being charged. Additionally, there is no proper follow-up with students regarding pending homework or academic progress. Overall, there is a lack of academic discipline and accountability",
